Been reading some of the comments on here. Its called an Auto Pulse. Our service carries them on the ambulances. They are simply a tool. They work very well and  they do great compressions. With that being said, nothing is perfect. There are contraindications and sometimes you have to do good ole manual compressions. Nothing will ever replace the hands and brain of a good EMT / Medic.
I'm concerned about some of you... the video clearly says to continue compressions on the move. It didn't say to replace humans doing regular cpr.

You see the Burnese mountain dogs? Thanks to proper breeding those dogs are having less and less health problems. 30 years ago they didn't live very long and had serious problems with their hind legs and muscles. They were also very susceptible to cancer and tumors. Thanks to proper breeding of healthy lines we now have healthier dogs. Breeding is not bad. Improper breeding is bad.

I know this is a positive video, but I feel led to say that pets are a life-long responsibility, not a cute accessory. Too many people go and get a puppy (or any pet) because it's adorable, and then they discover they can't/won't take the time to give them proper care and training. Be informed, people.  <3
